</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jeffrey A. Perlman and Dennis McLellan 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PINATAS: They're traditional and festive, yes, but "a lot of people complain 
about the violence of hitting a pinata," says Santa Ana pinata merchant Oscar 
Vargas. . . . Vargas' solution: A kinder, gentler pinata. . . . Participants 
take turns picking and pulling on strings hanging from the bottom. Tug the 
right one and the pinata pops open. . . . Cinco de Mayo celebrations make this 
one of the busiest times of the year for pinata makers. Jeffrey A. Perlman and 
Dennis McLellan 
</P>
</TEXT>
